trans-unit.source: Create or update a Traffic Manager profile
trans-unit.target: Create or update a Traffic Manager profile

trans-unit.source: Create or update a Traffic Manager profile within a resource group.
trans-unit.target: Create or update a Traffic Manager profile within a resource group.

trans-unit.source: See <link xlink:href="d066cb34-75f0-46ff-9881-4e6b5d87d3da#bk_common" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Common parameters and headers</link> for headers and parameters that are used by all requests related to Traffic Manager profiles.
trans-unit.target: See <link xlink:href="d066cb34-75f0-46ff-9881-4e6b5d87d3da#bk_common" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Common parameters and headers</link> for headers and parameters that are used by all requests related to Traffic Manager profiles.

trans-unit.source: Replace {profile-name} with the name of the Traffic Manager profile to be created.
trans-unit.target: Replace {profile-name} with the name of the Traffic Manager profile to be created.

trans-unit.source: The profile name must be unique within the resource group.
trans-unit.target: The profile name must be unique within the resource group.

trans-unit.source: Specifies whether the profile should be enabled or disabled
trans-unit.target: Specifies whether the profile should be enabled or disabled

trans-unit.source: This parameter is optional, default value ‘Enabled’
trans-unit.target: This parameter is optional, default value ‘Enabled’

trans-unit.source: Specifies the traffic routing method, used to determine which endpoint is returned in response to incoming DNS queries.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the traffic routing method, used to determine which endpoint is returned in response to incoming DNS queries.

trans-unit.source: Container for DNS settings for this Traffic Manager profile.
trans-unit.target: Container for DNS settings for this Traffic Manager profile.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the relative DNS name provided by this Traffic Manager profile.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the relative DNS name provided by this Traffic Manager profile.

trans-unit.source: This value is combined with the DNS domain name used by Azure Traffic Manager to form the fully-qualified domain name (FQDN) of the profile.Cannot be modified once set.
trans-unit.target: This value is combined with the DNS domain name used by Azure Traffic Manager to form the fully-qualified domain name (FQDN) of the profile.Cannot be modified once set.

trans-unit.source: The fully-qualified domain name of the Traffic Manager profile.
trans-unit.target: The fully-qualified domain name of the Traffic Manager profile.

trans-unit.source: This is a read-only property, formed from the concatenation of the relativeName with the DNS domain used by Azure Traffic Manager.
trans-unit.target: This is a read-only property, formed from the concatenation of the relativeName with the DNS domain used by Azure Traffic Manager.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the DNS Time-to-Live (TTL), in seconds.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the DNS Time-to-Live (TTL), in seconds.

trans-unit.source: This informs the Local DNS resolvers and DNS clients how long to cache DNS responses provided by this Traffic Manager profile.Possible values are 30…999,999.
trans-unit.target: This informs the Local DNS resolvers and DNS clients how long to cache DNS responses provided by this Traffic Manager profile.Possible values are 30…999,999.

trans-unit.source: Container for endpoint monitoring settings for this Traffic Manager profile.
trans-unit.target: Container for endpoint monitoring settings for this Traffic Manager profile.

trans-unit.source: Indicates the overall health status for the Traffic Manager profile.
trans-unit.target: Indicates the overall health status for the Traffic Manager profile.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the protocol to use to monitor endpoint health.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the protocol to use to monitor endpoint health.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the TCP port used to monitor endpoint health.Possible values are 1…65535
trans-unit.target: Specifies the TCP port used to monitor endpoint health.Possible values are 1…65535

trans-unit.source: Specifies the path relative to the endpoint domain name used to probe for endpoint health.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the path relative to the endpoint domain name used to probe for endpoint health.

trans-unit.source: Specifies an array of Traffic Manager endpoints
trans-unit.target: Specifies an array of Traffic Manager endpoints

trans-unit.source: Specifies the name of the endpoint
trans-unit.target: Specifies the name of the endpoint

trans-unit.source: Specifies the type of the endpoint.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the type of the endpoint.

trans-unit.source: The Azure Resource Manager API for Traffic Manager is currently in Preview mode and the only supported type is “Microsoft.Network/TrafficManagerProfiles/ExternalEndpoints”
trans-unit.target: The Azure Resource Manager API for Traffic Manager is currently in Preview mode and the only supported type is “Microsoft.Network/TrafficManagerProfiles/ExternalEndpoints”

trans-unit.source: Container for settings relating to this Traffic Manager endpoint.
trans-unit.target: Container for settings relating to this Traffic Manager endpoint.

trans-unit.source: The fully-qualified DNS name of the endpoint.
trans-unit.target: The fully-qualified DNS name of the endpoint.

trans-unit.source: Traffic Manager returns this value in DNS responses to direct traffic to this endpoint.
trans-unit.target: Traffic Manager returns this value in DNS responses to direct traffic to this endpoint.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the status of the endpoint.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the status of the endpoint.

trans-unit.source: If the endpoint is Enabled, it is probed for endpoint health and is included in the traffic routing method.
trans-unit.target: If the endpoint is Enabled, it is probed for endpoint health and is included in the traffic routing method.

trans-unit.source: This parameter is optional, default value ‘Enabled’.
trans-unit.target: This parameter is optional, default value ‘Enabled’.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the weight assigned by Traffic Manager to the endpoint.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the weight assigned by Traffic Manager to the endpoint.

trans-unit.source: This is only used if the Traffic Manager profile is configured to use the 'weighted' traffic routing method.Possible values are from 1 to 1000.
trans-unit.target: This is only used if the Traffic Manager profile is configured to use the 'weighted' traffic routing method.Possible values are from 1 to 1000.

trans-unit.source: This parameter is optional, if omitted a default weight of ‘1’ is used.
trans-unit.target: This parameter is optional, if omitted a default weight of ‘1’ is used.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the priority of this endpoint when using the ‘priority’ traffic routing method.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the priority of this endpoint when using the ‘priority’ traffic routing method.

trans-unit.source: Priority must lie in the range 1…1000.
trans-unit.target: Priority must lie in the range 1…1000.

trans-unit.source: If specified, it must be specified on all endpoints, and no two endpoints can share the same priority value.
trans-unit.target: If specified, it must be specified on all endpoints, and no two endpoints can share the same priority value.

trans-unit.source: If omitted, Traffic Manager assigns endpoints with default priority values 1, 2, 3 etc in the order the endpoints are provided.
trans-unit.target: If omitted, Traffic Manager assigns endpoints with default priority values 1, 2, 3 etc in the order the endpoints are provided.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the location of the external endpoint, for use with the ‘Performance’ traffic routing method.This parameter is optional, but it must be specified for endpoints of the type "ExternalEndpoint" in a profile that has the load balancing method set to "Performance".For more information and possible values, see <externalLink><linkText>List all of the available geo-locations</linkText><linkUri>https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/azure/dn790540.aspx</linkUri></externalLink>
trans-unit.target: Specifies the location of the external endpoint, for use with the ‘Performance’ traffic routing method.This parameter is optional, but it must be specified for endpoints of the type "ExternalEndpoint" in a profile that has the load balancing method set to "Performance".For more information and possible values, see <externalLink><linkText>List all of the available geo-locations</linkText><linkUri>https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/azure/dn790540.aspx</linkUri></externalLink>

trans-unit.source: Indicates the health status for the endpoint.
trans-unit.target: Indicates the health status for the endpoint.

trans-unit.source: See <externalLink><linkText>About Traffic Manager Monitoring</linkText><linkUri>http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/gg441293.aspx</linkUri></externalLink> for further details.
trans-unit.target: See <externalLink><linkText>About Traffic Manager Monitoring</linkText><linkUri>http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/gg441293.aspx</linkUri></externalLink> for further details.
